Hangnail - A hangnail or agnail is a small, torn piece of skin next to a fingernail or toenail.
hangnail definition: a bit of skin hanging loose at the side or root of a fingernail.

wiki.text:
A 'hangnail' or 'agnail' (also known as a 'stepmother's blessing'<ref
name="oed"></ref>) is a small, torn piece of skin next to a fingernail or
toenail. Unlike whitlows, hangnails are usually caused by dry skin or nail
biting and may be prevented with proper moisturization of the skin.
